While researching to see how to interpret the make ahead option - it looks like the best thing to do is to combine everything, but don't bake it. Then bake it in full the day of the meal.

note from Serious Eats: - https://www.seriouseats.com/recipes/2010/11/classic-sage-and-sausage-stuffing-or-dressing-recipe.html 
>>"The stuffing can be prepared through step 3 and placed in a greased baking dish a day in advance. Remove from the refrigerator and allow the stuffing to come to room temperature for at least 1 hour before baking the next day."
